net.sourceforge.waters.model.module

Interface ConstantAliasProxy

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AliasProxy, Comparable<NamedProxy>, ComparableProxy<NamedProxy>, IdentifiedProxy, NamedProxy, Proxy
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ConstantAliasElement

    public interface ConstantAliasProxy
extends AliasProxy

    An alias representing a constant definition.

    A constant alias is used to assign a simple constant to a name. The name of a constant alias must be a simple identifier (SimpleIdentifierProxy).

    A constant alias may be a parameter, in which case the value in the declaration only is a default that can be overridden by instantiation from another module. A parameter can be optional or required: for required parameters, a value must be provided when instantiating. Nevertheless, even required parameters must have a default value, which is used when compiling the module on its own.

    Author:
    Robi Malik

        ScopeKind getScope()
        Gets the scope of this alias declaration. The scope defines whether this alias actually is a parameter.
        Returns:
        One of ScopeKind.LOCAL, ScopeKind.OPTIONAL_PARAMETER, or ScopeKind.REQUIRED_PARAMETER.
